# Remote Sensing Scene Classification Project

## Project Overview

The Remote Sensing Scene Classification Project is a deep learning-based image classification system designed to automatically recognize and categorize satellite and aerial images into different land-use and scene categories. The main objective of the project is to analyze remote sensing imagery and identify the type of environment or geographical region represented in the image. The system can classify scenes such as airports, forests, beaches, rivers, residential areas, industrial zones, mountains, farmlands, deserts, bridges, stadiums, and many other categories.

This project combines concepts from Artificial Intelligence, Computer Vision, Deep Learning, and Remote Sensing to build an intelligent classification system capable of understanding high-resolution satellite imagery. The project demonstrates how convolutional neural networks (CNNs) can be applied in real-world applications such as environmental monitoring, urban planning, military surveillance, agriculture analysis, disaster management, and geographic information systems.

---

# Problem Statement

Remote sensing images contain large amounts of visual information collected from satellites and aerial sensors. Manually analyzing these images is difficult, time-consuming, and requires domain experts. Traditional image processing techniques are often unable to handle the complexity and variation found in remote sensing scenes.

The purpose of this project is to automate the process of scene recognition using deep learning models capable of extracting high-level spatial features from satellite images and accurately classifying them into predefined scene categories.

---

# Dataset Used

The project uses the NWPU-RESISC45 Dataset dataset, which is one of the most popular benchmark datasets for remote sensing scene classification research.

The dataset contains:

* 31,500 remote sensing images
* 45 scene categories
* 700 images per category
* High-resolution aerial and satellite images
* Diverse environmental and geographical scenes

Some example scene classes include:

* Airport
* Beach
* Bridge
* Church
* Commercial Area
* Dense Residential
* Desert
* Farmland
* Forest
* Golf Course
* Harbor
* Industrial Area
* Lake
* Mountain
* Parking Lot
* Railway Station
* Residential Area
* River
* Stadium
* Storage Tanks
* Tennis Court

The dataset is challenging because images within the same class may look very different, while images from different classes may appear visually similar.

---

# Project Objectives

The main objectives of the project were:

* Build an accurate remote sensing scene classification system
* Train multiple deep learning models and compare their performance
* Apply transfer learning to improve classification accuracy
* Reduce overfitting using data augmentation and regularization techniques
* Visualize model predictions using Grad-CAM
* Deploy the trained model into an interactive web application
* Optimize models for lightweight and efficient inference

---

